{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, it is tempting for researchers to explore the extent to which open-source LLMs are capable for text annotation tasks.",
    "In addition to cost-effectiveness, open-source LLMs are increasingly recognized for their transparency, reproducibility, and enhanced data protection features [27,36].",
    "However, the academic benchmarks reported above lack the text annotation tasks, especially that of political text.",
    "To assess how well open-source LLMs perform in text annotation tasks, we compare GPT (3.5 & 4) results with those of LLaMA (1 & 2), Llama-3 (8b) and FLAN (T5 XL).",
    "Considering the reported training data size, scaled-up parameters, and reading comprehension benchmarks, we expect the Llama-2 (70b) model to perform well on our text annotation tasks.Figure 4 compares the text annotation accuracy of GPT-4, GPT -3.5, LLaMA-1 (HuggingChat), LLaMA-1 (30b), LLaMA-2 (13b), LLaMA-2 (70b), Llama-3 (8b), FLAN-T5 (XL), and MTurkers."
  ]
}